summary:
as someone who struggles with body image and disordered eating who didn't find Dan's joke offensive, i have to say...
you are...
body:
as someone who struggles with body image and disordered eating who didn’t find Dan’s joke offensive, i have to say…

you are not in the wrong if you found what he said to be harmful, insensitive, upsetting or offensive. you are justified in feeling that way! and i totally understand why! but i’m not going to use my experience against anyone or invalidate other people’s feelings, and neither should you. doesn’t matter if you struggle with it or not, just cause YOU aren’t offended, it doesn’t mean everyone who IS offended is invalid.

it’s okay to criticize your role models.

summary:
yall acting like we ain't been knew our fave is problematic 
He always has and probably always will toe that line of what's...
body:
yall acting like we ain’t been knew our fave is problematic

He always has and probably always will toe that line of what’s acceptable. He’s tame compared to when he was little and he seems to try to genuinely try to learn from his mistakes. It’s fine to try to show him the error of his ways, but I don’t think genuine anger is warranted because he obviously didn’t intend it maliciously. Hes a dumbass, but hes trying and that’s all you can ask of someone. We’re all human
